@@rsteaming faintly with infernal heat. Across the river lies the first true
@@rcircle of Hell. The ancient ferryman Charon poles his skiff through the
@@rmurk, his hollow eyes burning with ember-light. The wails of the waiting
@@rdamned rise like a tide from the far bank. Coins glint on the eyes of newly
@@rarrived shades, placed there by the living to pay the ferryman's toll. Those
