@@rvirtuous unbaptized wander here in a state of perpetual melancholy, denied
@@rthe joys of Heaven yet spared the tortures further below. Ancient heroes
@@rand philosophers drift past, their faces etched with noble sadness. The
@@rair is still and cool compared to the inferno below. Great marble halls
@@rrise here half-collapsed, the libraries and academies of a civilization
@@rthat never reached its potential. Aristotle sits in a corner writing
@@rformulae that solve nothing, and Virgil watches with an expression of
@@rprofound and dignified regret. Even the light here is grey and beautiful.
