#1632
The Abyssal Antechamber~
@@rA vast antechamber opens here before the approach to the pit of Abaddon.
@@rThe walls are pierced by hundreds of small openings through which the
@@rlocusts of the abyss pour in streams, circling the chamber in patterns
@@rthat would mean something to someone with the wrong kind of education.
@@rThe floor is thick with the shed carapaces of countless insects, creating
@@ra crackling carpet that catches the lurid light filtering down from
@@rabove. Greater demons stand at attention here, their attention fixed on
@@rthe pit entrance as if standing guard against something trying to get
@@rOUT as much as keeping things from getting in. The air has a metallic
@@rquality like blood and ozone, and every breath tastes of the abyss.
