#1634
The Chamber of Final Judgment~
@@rThis round chamber sits directly beneath the Throne Room of Beelzebub.
@@rIts floor is a mosaic of damned souls rendered in infernal tile, their
@@rfaces arranged in expressions of various stages of acceptance. The walls
@@rare covered in proclamations of judgment written in hellfire, each one
@@rspecific to a single soul now serving its assigned torment. A raised
@@rdais in the center bears the scales used to weigh the sins of the
@@rdamned -- enormous iron scales taller than a house, their pans still
@@rshowing the slight tilt of the last judgment rendered. The chains holding
@@rthe pans move slightly, as if the scales are still being calibrated for
@@rthe next case. The chamber smells of justice, which smells exactly like
@@rburning paper and absolutely nothing else.
