#1635
The Crucible of Torment~
@@rA massive stone chamber dominated by a central crucible of hellfire in
@@rwhich the sins of the living are rendered into fuel for the torments of
@@rthe dead. Greater demons tend this crucible with professional reverence,
@@radding materials from sealed iron containers brought by chains of damned
@@rporters. The heat is constant and focused and has a particular quality
@@rthat seems to penetrate armor and conviction equally. Channels carved
@@rinto the floor carry the rendered product away to various parts of Hell,
@@rthe system arranged with the logic of industrial infrastructure. Signs
@@rposted above each channel indicate their destinations in a script that
@@rwould take a scholar of the forbidden texts several lifetimes to decode,
@@rassuming they had several lifetimes available, which they would not.
