The Antechamber of the Fallen~
@@rA broad antechamber opens before the approach to Lucifer's Throne Room.
@@rThe walls here are hung with tapestries woven from the hair of damned
@@rsouls, their colors still vivid despite their origins. The tapestries
@@rdepict the story of the Fall in heroic scale -- the battle in Heaven,
@@rthe plummet through the void, the arrival in Hell -- all rendered with
@@ra kind of terrible grandeur that suggests the artist sympathized with
@@rthe subject. Stone benches line the walls where greater demons sit in
@@rwhat might be called a waiting room if the concept were not incongruously
@@rdignified for its location. The doors at the far end are solid iron
@@rand tall enough for a giant, their surfaces carved with images of what
@@rwas lost and what was found and how those two things relate.
