#1638
The Library of Forbidden Truths~
@@rA vast library fills this chamber, its shelves carved from the bones
@@rof angels who refused to fall and were broken for their resistance.
@@rThe books here contain truths that cannot be known by the living without
@@rcost -- the real names of demons, the original text of laws that have
@@rbeen revised, the histories of events that were witnessed and then
@@runwitnessed. Fallen angels serve as librarians, their wings folded close
@@ras they glide between the shelves in silence. The books themselves are
@@rchained to their shelves, but the chains are not locked -- they are
@@rpresent only to mark which books are checked out and which remain.
@@rThe reading tables are lit by globes of captive starlight, which is the
@@ronly natural light visible anywhere in Hell and which has a quality of
@@rprofound sadness for that reason.
