#1639
The Corridor of Endless Descent~
@@rA long corridor slopes steadily downward here, its incline so gradual
@@rit is only apparent over distance. The walls are scored with depth
@@rmarkings in a scale that does not correspond to any known measurement
@@rsystem, counting downward in a sequence that has been going long enough
@@rthat the numbers are very large indeed. The floor is worn smooth by
@@rmillions of feet. Somewhere far ahead and below, the slope levels out
@@rinto something that has not been named yet because naming would require
@@racknowledging it, which the scholars who constructed this place preferred
@@rnot to do. The air grows heavier as you descend. The light from behind
@@rfades. The light ahead begins as a distant red glow and grows.
