#1651
The Shore of the Lustful~
@@rThe shore of the second circle's storm-sea lies here, its sand the deep
@@rred of rust and dried blood. The storm above rages without pause, sending
@@rits victims crashing into the sand before snatching them skyward again.
@@rShattered fragments of the shades' memories materialize here as objects
@@rthat dissolve when touched -- flowers, letters, faces -- appearing and
@@rdisappearing in an endless exhibition of things that mattered once and
@@rmatter still, which is the cruelest detail of this particular torment.
@@rLust demons haunt this shore, feeding on the lingering emotional resonance
@@rof what the damned carry with them. They are beautiful in the way that
@@rpoisonous things are beautiful, which is completely and on purpose.
