#1680
The Bolgia of Thieves~
@@rThe ninth bolgia of Malebolge writhes with thieves and robbers, each one
@@rconstantly transforming -- serpents bite at humans who dissolve and reform
@@ras serpents themselves, endlessly exchanging shapes. The metamorphosis is
@@rnever comfortable and never complete, always arrested at the most unpleasant
@@rmidpoint. The ground is carpeted with shed skins and scales that crumble to
@@rash underfoot. A few half-human shapes crawl the edges of the trench, their
@@ridentity so thoroughly confused by transformation that they have forgotten
@@rwhich form is theirs originally. They reach for each other with hands that
@@rbecome claws before they can grip. The serpents move with confident territorial
@@rpurpose among the confusion, the only stable things in a bolgia defined by flux.
